## Bootrom

bootrom会寻找eflash中的镜像，如果没有从qflash中copy manifest镜像到eflash，从eflah中启动

- eflash类似于xip的操作，读可以通过总线读，写是flash操作

- manifest包含镜像所必须的信息，bootrom从manifest区域获取镜像入口地址，从qflash中拷贝镜像到eflash
  
  - 镜像经tar工具封装，命名为matcha-tock-bundle.bin
  
  - bootrom解析镜像名称，并拷贝tar包中的镜像主体到eflash的起始地址处

## 镜像制作校验

由bootrom可知，bl镜像需经tar打包，并封装为matcha-tock-bundle.bin，除此以外，bl与firmware镜像制作过程一致，如下图所示：

![avatar][img1]

- 注意上述镜像制作过程，one img section中header、payload区域使用sha256计算得出hash值保存在TLV区域

img header如下图所示

![avatar][img2]

具体的数据格式为：

```c
#define IMAGE_F_RAM_LOAD 0x00000020
#define IMAGE_F_BOOTLOADER 0x80000000 /* img type is bootloader */
#define IMAGE_F_ENTRY 0x40000000 /* section contains entry */
#define IMAGE_F_LOAD_RAM 0x20000000 /* image should be loaded to RAM */

/** Image header.  All fields are in little endian byte order. */
struct image_header {
    uint32_t ih_magic;//0x0
    uint32_t ih_load_addr;//0x4
    uint16_t ih_hdr_size; /* Size of image header (bytes).0x8 */
    uint16_t ih_protect_tlv_size; /* Size of protected TLV area (bytes). 0xa*/
    uint32_t ih_img_size; /* Does not include header.0xc */
    uint32_t ih_flags; /* IMAGE_F_[...]. 0x10*/
    struct image_version ih_ver;//0x14
    uint32_t _pad1//0x1c;
};

struct image_version {
    uint8_t iv_major;
    uint8_t iv_minor;
    uint16_t iv_revision;
    uint32_t iv_build_num;
};
```

tlv区域为：

![avatar][img3]

具体的数据格式为：

```c
#define IMAGE_TLV_KEYHASH 0x01 /* hash of the public key */
#define IMAGE_TLV_PUBKEY 0x02 /* public key */
#define IMAGE_TLV_SHA256 0x10 /* SHA256 of image hdr and body */
#define IMAGE_TLV_RSA2048_PSS 0x20 /* RSA2048 of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ECDSA224 0x21 /* ECDSA of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ECDSA256 0x22 /* ECDSA of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_RSA3072_PSS 0x23 /* RSA3072 of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ED25519 0x24 /* ed25519 of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_RSA2048 0x30 /* Key encrypted with RSA-OAEP-2048 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_KW128 0x31 /* Key encrypted with AES-KW-128 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_EC256 0x32 /* Key encrypted with ECIES-EC256 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_X25519 0x33 /* Key encrypted with ECIES-X25519 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_DEPENDENCY 0x40 /* Image depends on other image */
#define IMAGE_TLV_SEC_CNT 0x50 /* security counter */
#define IMAGE_TLV_BOOT_RECORD 0x60 /* measured boot record */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ANY 0xffff /* Used to iterate over all TLV */

/** Image TLV header.  All fields in little endian. */
struct image_tlv_info {
    uint16_t it_magic;
    uint16_t it_tlv_tot; /* size of TLV area (including tlv_info header) */
};

/** Image trailer TLV format. All fields in little endian. */
struct image_tlv {
    uint16_t it_type; /* IMAGE_TLV_[...]. */
    uint16_t it_len; /* Data length (not including TLV header). */
};


typedef struct ImgTlvInfo
{
    struct image_tlv_info info;//0x0
    struct image_tlv tlv_type_len;//0x4
    hash//0x8开始的hash区域，sha256计算header tailer得到的32字节hash区域
} ImgTlvInfo;
```

- bl镜像lma在qflash处0x0开始的256k区域，vma在eflash开始的256k以及ram_main，升级时存放在eflash中256k往后的地址区域
- app镜像lma在qflash处256k后的区域，vma在ram_smc处
- bl与app的lma、vma均不会重叠，不会发生冲突

## xmodem下载

### 简介

Xmodem协议是串口通信中广泛使用到的异步文件传输协议，以128字节块的形式传输数据，并且每个块都使用一个校验过程来进行错误检测。在校验过程中如果接收方关于一个块的检验和与它在发送方的检验相同时，接收方就向发送方发送一个确认字节ACK。如果有错则发送一个字节NAK要求重发。以保证传输过程中的正确性，但是由于需要对每个块都要进行检验，显得效率比较低

### 数据帧

![avatar][img4]

Xmodem协议的传输数据单位为信息包，包含一个标题开始字符SOH或者STX，一个单字节包序号，一个单字节包包序号的补码，128个字节数据和一个双字节的CRC16校验

![avatar][img5]

对于标准Xmodem协议来说，如果传送的文件不是128的整数倍，那么最后一个数据包的有效内容肯定小于帧长，不足的部分需要用CTRL-Z(0x1A)来填充

### 传输过程

Xmodem协议的传输由接收方启动，接收方向发送方发送C或者NAK（这里的NAK是用来启动传输的。下面我们用到的NAK是用来对数据产生重传机制）。其中接收方发送NAK信号表示接收方打算用累加和校验；发送字符C则表示接收方打算使用CRC校验。  
Uart_SendData(INST_LPUART1, &C, 1); //发送Xmodem帧传输开始命令

![avatar][img6]

当接收方发送的第一个C或者NAK到达发送方，发送方认为可以发送第一个数据包了，传输启动。发送方接着接着应该将数据以每次128字节的数据加上包头，包号，包号补码，末尾加上校验和，打包成帧格式传送。发送方发了第一个包后就等待接收方的确认字节ACK，收到接收方传来的ACK确认，就认为数据包被接收方正确接收，并且接收方要求发送方继续发送下一个包；如果发送方收到接收方传来的NAK（这里的表示重发），则表示接收方请求重发刚才的数据包；如果发送方收到接收方传来的CAN字节，则表示接收方请求无条件停止传输。  
如果发送方正常传输完全部数据，需要结束传输，正常结束需要发送方发送EOT通知接收方。接收方回以ACK进行确认。如果接收方发送CAN给发送方也可以强制停止传输，发送方受到CAN后不需要发送EOT确认，此时传输已经结束

### 注意

在编写库时候，Uart应该加入时间，timeout设定，否则Uart接受一直堵塞，无法接收新的数据；此外xmodem支持1024字节的数据包

### 工具命令

linux平台:

1. picocom。命令如下：`sudo picocom --send-cmd "sx -vv -k" --receive-cmd "rx -vv" -b 115200 /dev/ttyUSBx`，进入串口后ctrl a + ctrl s选择镜像传输。
2. minicom。进入minicom界面后调出控制界面，选择configure minicom，在configuration界面选择File transfer protocols,在传输协议界面上的xmodem传输命令中加上-k选项以支持xmodem 1k的传输协议。

![avatar][img7]

**注意：**  
linux上minicom或者picocom本身不支持xmodem、ymodem、zmodem等传输协议，传输协议基于lrzsz工具集，上述提到的-k选项是在lrzsz中支持1k传输。

## Debug

- xmodem下载失败
  ----------
  
  - 此类问题可能源于crc校验失败、接收一帧数据后烧写失败等。由于xmodem下载时串口需要配合xmodem时序，不能使用串口打印此时信息，使用jtag调试也难以配合时序，所以推荐使用写内存的方式debug。保持机器一直上电，ram在上电时一直有效，通过写内存记录程序的执行流，等到xmodem下载结束后打印出内存信息
  
  - 此外，在xmodem下载时串口不应为阻塞接受模式。如果xmodem下载不稳定，可以考虑在在串口接收中加入延时

- bl下载app后无法正常boot
  ----------------
  
  - 此问题可能得原因是flash读写失败、app镜像格式不正确、链接脚本设计不当等，调试方法如下：
  
  - 读出flash中相应地址的数据，与镜像比对，查看镜像是否写入，排除flash读写的原因
  
  - 若app镜像写入到flash中正确位置，可以考虑app镜像存在问题，使用jtag debug app.out，看看app.out是否能够执行
  
  - 如果jtag下app.out能执行，但镜像无法boot，可以考虑链接脚本等原因导致镜像制作不当，此时常规方法难以debug，bootloader跳入APP可能串口打印失败，在此推荐使用写内存的方式。在app程序中写内存记录程序执行流，使用bootloader下载app，bootloader boot app，之后可以通过jtag或者编写程序读出内存中相应值判断程序在哪出错了

- xmodem下载从第一帧开始就无法接收到ACK
  -----------------------
  
  - 此类问题一般出自xmodem发送、接收方接收一帧数据允许的延时不一致。由于xmodem发送可能在windows、linux或者其他平台，不同平台xmodem下载的时序不一致，板子代码难以同时匹配这么多种情况。此类问题一般可以通过修改板子代码中xmodem下载中延时参数解决

- 烧写bl镜像后bl镜像无法boot
  -----------------
  
  - 与第二个bug类似，可以沿用debug方法，在此提供另一种debug方法
  
  - 如下，在链接脚本程序段上封装flash page用以跳过imgtool封装的镜像头、镜像尾，用此种方式制作的镜像与out文件类似，out文件与镜像各个程序段所在地址相同，所以可以用bl.out下载bl镜像后gdb跳转到bl镜像的起始处，或者尝试直接用gdb调试bl镜像

```c
  __VECTOR_VMA_BASE = __MANIFEST_VMA_END + __FLASH_PAGE_SIZE;
  __VECTOR_LMA_BASE = __MANIFEST_LMA_END + __FLASH_PAGE_SIZE;
  .vectors __VECTOR_VMA_BASE : AT(__VECTOR_LMA_BASE) {
    _text_start = .;
    *(.vectors)
    . = ALIGN(256);
  }
  __VECTOR_SECTION_SIZE = SIZEOF(.vectors);
  __VECTOR_SECTION_PAGES = __VECTOR_SECTION_SIZE / __FLASH_PAGE_SIZE;
  __VECTOR_SECTION_PAGES += (((__VECTOR_SECTION_SIZE % __FLASH_PAGE_SIZE) > 0 ) ? 1 : 0);
  __VECTOR_SECTION_PAGES += 1; /* skip trailer */
  __VECTOR_VMA_END = __VECTOR_VMA_BASE + __FLASH_PAGE_SIZE * __VECTOR_SECTION_PAGES;
  __VECTOR_LMA_END = __VECTOR_LMA_BASE + __FLASH_PAGE_SIZE * __VECTOR_SECTION_PAGES;
```

# 附加工具

1. 解析镜像工具

```c
//main.c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdint.h>
#include <string.h>
#include "sha256.h"

#define IMAGE_MAGIC 0x96f3b83d
#define IMAGE_MAGIC_V1 0x96f3b83d
#define IMAGE_MAGIC_NONE 0xffffffff
#define IMAGE_TLV_INFO_MAGIC 0x6907
#define IMAGE_TLV_PROT_INFO_MAGIC 0x6908

#define IMAGE_F_RAM_LOAD 0x00000020
#define IMAGE_F_BOOTLOADER 0x80000000 /* img type is bootloader */
#define IMAGE_F_ENTRY 0x40000000      /* section contains entry */
#define IMAGE_F_LOAD_RAM 0x20000000   /* image should be loaded to RAM */

#define IMAGE_TLV_KEYHASH 0x01     /* hash of the public key */
#define IMAGE_TLV_PUBKEY 0x02      /* public key */
#define IMAGE_TLV_SHA256 0x10      /* SHA256 of image hdr and body */
#define IMAGE_TLV_RSA2048_PSS 0x20 /* RSA2048 of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ECDSA224 0x21    /* ECDSA of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ECDSA256 0x22    /* ECDSA of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_RSA3072_PSS 0x23 /* RSA3072 of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ED25519 0x24     /* ed25519 of hash output */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_RSA2048 0x30 /* Key encrypted with RSA-OAEP-2048 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_KW128 0x31   /* Key encrypted with AES-KW-128 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_EC256 0x32   /* Key encrypted with ECIES-EC256 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ENC_X25519 0x33  /* Key encrypted with ECIES-X25519 */
#define IMAGE_TLV_DEPENDENCY 0x40  /* Image depends on other image */
#define IMAGE_TLV_SEC_CNT 0x50     /* security counter */
#define IMAGE_TLV_BOOT_RECORD 0x60 /* measured boot record */
#define IMAGE_TLV_ANY 0xffff       /* Used to iterate over all TLV */

struct image_version
{
    uint8_t iv_major;
    uint8_t iv_minor;
    uint16_t iv_revision;
    uint32_t iv_build_num;
};

struct image_header
{
    uint32_t ih_magic;
    uint32_t ih_load_addr;
    uint16_t ih_hdr_size;         /* Size of image header (bytes). */
    uint16_t ih_protect_tlv_size; /* Size of protected TLV area (bytes). */
    uint32_t ih_img_size;         /* Does not include header. */
    uint32_t ih_flags;            /* IMAGE_F_[...]. */
    struct image_version ih_ver;
    uint32_t _pad1;
};

/** Image TLV header.  All fields in little endian. */
struct image_tlv_info
{
    uint16_t it_magic;
    uint16_t it_tlv_tot; /* size of TLV area (including tlv_info header) */
};

/** Image trailer TLV format. All fields in little endian. */
struct image_tlv
{
    uint16_t it_type; /* IMAGE_TLV_[...]. */
    uint16_t it_len;  /* Data length (not including TLV header). */
};

typedef struct ImgTlvInfo
{
    struct image_tlv_info info;
    struct image_tlv tlv_type_len;
} ImgTlvInfo;

/* flag helps analysis img */
typedef enum
{
    INITIAL = 0,
    FIND_HEADER = 1,
    FIND_TLV = 2,
} ImgFlag;

typedef struct ImgStatus
{
    uint32_t end_addr;
    ImgFlag flag; /* flag for img status*/
} ImgStatus;

static void echo_img_section(struct image_header *img_header)
{
    printf("-------------------------\n");
    printf("Info:section vma=0x%x\n", img_header->ih_load_addr);
    printf("Info:section size=%d\n", img_header->ih_img_size);
    printf("Info:section loading...\n");
    printf("-------------------------\n");
}

static void echo_tlv_info(ImgTlvInfo img_tlv_info)
{
    printf("tlv_magic:0x%x, tlv_size:0x%x, it_type:0x%x, it_len:0x%x\n", img_tlv_info.info.it_magic, img_tlv_info.info.it_tlv_tot, img_tlv_info.tlv_type_len.it_type, img_tlv_info.tlv_type_len.it_len);
}

void verify_hash(uint8_t *img_hash, uint8_t *compute_hash, uint32_t size)
{
    uint32_t i;
    printf("    img_hash:");
    for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
        printf("%x", img_hash[i]);
    printf("\ncompute_hash:");
    for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
        printf("%x", img_hash[i]);
    if (memcmp(img_hash, compute_hash, size) != 0)
        printf("\nVerify failed!\n");
    else
        printf("\nVerify success!\n");
}

int main(int argc, char *argv[])
{
    uint8_t buf[256], compute_hash[32], img_hash[32];
    uint32_t i;
    Sha256 sha256;
    FILE *img_file;
    struct image_header img_header;
    ImgStatus img_status;
    ImgTlvInfo img_tlv_info;

    if (argc < 2)
    {
        printf("%s <img file>\n", argv[0]);
        return 0;
    }
    img_file = fopen(argv[1], "rb");
    if (img_file == NULL)
    {
        printf("fopen error\n");
        return 0;
    }
    sha256_init(&sha256);
    img_status.flag = INITIAL;
    for (i = 0; i < 10000; i++)
    {
        int res = fread(buf, 1, sizeof(buf), img_file);
        if (res <= 0)
            break;
        if (img_status.flag == INITIAL)
        {
            memcpy((uint8_t *)&img_header, buf, sizeof(struct image_header));
            if (img_header.ih_magic == IMAGE_MAGIC)
            {
                img_status.flag = FIND_HEADER;
                img_status.end_addr = img_header.ih_img_size +
                                      img_header.ih_hdr_size +
                                      i * sizeof(buf);
                if ((img_header.ih_flags & IMAGE_F_ENTRY) == IMAGE_F_ENTRY)
                {
                    if ((img_header.ih_flags & IMAGE_F_BOOTLOADER) ==
                        IMAGE_F_BOOTLOADER)
                        printf("Bootloader version:");
                    else
                        printf("Image version:");
                    printf("%d.%d.%d\n", img_header.ih_ver.iv_major,
                           img_header.ih_ver.iv_minor,
                           img_header.ih_ver.iv_revision);
                    printf("entry is 0x%x\n", img_header.ih_load_addr);
                }
                echo_img_section(&img_header);
                sha256_update(&sha256, buf, sizeof(buf));
            }
        }
        else if (img_status.flag == FIND_HEADER)
        {
            if (((i + 1) * sizeof(buf)) < img_status.end_addr)
            {
                sha256_update(&sha256, buf, sizeof(buf));
            }
            else
            {
                /* img end addr in current page */
                uint32_t len = img_status.end_addr - i * sizeof(buf);
                len = (len > sizeof(buf)) ? sizeof(buf) : len;
                uint32_t rest_len = sizeof(buf) - len;

                /* update rest len */
                sha256_update(&sha256, buf, len);
                sha256_final(&sha256, compute_hash);
                sha256_init(&sha256);
                if (rest_len != 0)
                {
                    memcpy((uint8_t *)&img_tlv_info, (uint8_t *)(buf + len), sizeof(ImgTlvInfo));
                    if (rest_len >= img_tlv_info.info.it_tlv_tot)
                    {
                        /* tlv area in current page */
                        memcpy(img_hash, buf + sizeof(ImgTlvInfo) + len, img_tlv_info.tlv_type_len.it_len);
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        /* TLV area appears between current page and next page */
                        uint32_t current_page_hash_len, next_page_hash_len;
                        next_page_hash_len = img_tlv_info.info.it_tlv_tot - rest_len;
                        current_page_hash_len = img_tlv_info.tlv_type_len.it_len - next_page_hash_len;
                        memcpy(img_hash, buf + len + sizeof(ImgTlvInfo), current_page_hash_len);
                        /* get next page buf */
                        fread(buf, 1, sizeof(buf), img_file);
                        memcpy(img_hash + current_page_hash_len, buf, next_page_hash_len);
                    }
                }
                else
                {
                    /* tlv area in next page start addr */
                    fread(buf, 1, sizeof(buf), img_file);
                    memcpy((uint8_t *)&img_tlv_info, (uint8_t *)buf, sizeof(ImgTlvInfo));
                    memcpy(img_hash, buf + sizeof(ImgTlvInfo), img_tlv_info.tlv_type_len.it_len);
                }
                echo_tlv_info(img_tlv_info);
                verify_hash(img_hash, compute_hash, sizeof(img_hash));
                img_status.flag = INITIAL;
            }
        }
    }
    printf("\n");
    fclose(img_file);
    return 0;
}

#include <string.h>

#define sigma1(a) (rotr((a), 2) ^ rotr((a), 13) ^ rotr((a), 22))
#define sigma2(a) (rotr((a), 6) ^ rotr((a), 11) ^ rotr((a), 25))
#define sigma3(a) (rotr((a), 7) ^ rotr((a), 18) ^ ((a) >> 3))
#define sigma4(a) (rotr((a), 17) ^ rotr((a), 19) ^ ((a) >> 10))

#define ch(a, b, c) (((a) & (b)) ^ ((~(a)) & (c)))
#define maj(a, b, c) (((a) & (b)) ^ ((a) & (c)) ^ ((b) & (c)))

static const uint32_t k256[64] = {
    0x428a2f98, 0x71374491, 0xb5c0fbcf, 0xe9b5dba5, 0x3956c25b, 0x59f111f1,
    0x923f82a4, 0xab1c5ed5, 0xd807aa98, 0x12835b01, 0x243185be, 0x550c7dc3,

    0x983e5152, 0xa831c66d, 0xb00327c8, 0xbf597fc7, 0xc6e00bf3, 0xd5a79147,
    0x06ca6351, 0x14292967, 0x27b70a85, 0x2e1b2138, 0x4d2c6dfc, 0x53380d13,
    0x650a7354, 0x766a0abb, 0x81c2c92e, 0x92722c85, 0xa2bfe8a1, 0xa81a664b,
    0xc24b8b70, 0xc76c51a3, 0xd192e819, 0xd6990624, 0xf40e3585, 0x106aa070,
    0x19a4c116, 0x1e376c08, 0x2748774c, 0x34b0bcb5, 0x391c0cb3, 0x4ed8aa4a,
    0x5b9cca4f, 0x682e6ff3, 0x748f82ee, 0x78a5636f, 0x84c87814, 0x8cc70208,
    0x90befffa, 0xa4506ceb, 0xbef9a3f7, 0xc67178f2};

static inline uint32_t rotr(uint32_t a, uint32_t n)
{
    return (((a) >> n) | ((a) << (32 - n)));
}

static inline uint32_t big_endian(const uint8_t **c)
{
    uint32_t n = 0;

    n = (((uint32_t)(*((*c)++))) << 24);
    n |= ((uint32_t)(*((*c)++)) << 16);
    n |= ((uint32_t)(*((*c)++)) << 8);
    n |= ((uint32_t)(*((*c)++)));
    return n;
}

static void compress(uint32_t *iv, const uint8_t *data)
{
    uint32_t a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h;
    uint32_t s0, s1, t1, t2, n, i;
    uint32_t work_space[16];

    a = iv[0];
    b = iv[1];
    c = iv[2];
    d = iv[3];
    e = iv[4];
    f = iv[5];
    g = iv[6];
    h = iv[7];

    for (i = 0; i < 16; ++i)
    {
        n = big_endian(&data);
        t1 = work_space[i] = n;
        t1 += h + sigma2(e) + ch(e, f, g) + k256[i];
        t2 = sigma1(a) + maj(a, b, c);
        h = g;
        g = f;
        f = e;
        e = d + t1;
        d = c;
        c = b;
        b = a;
        a = t1 + t2;
    }

    for (; i < 64; ++i)
    {
        s0 = work_space[(i + 1) & 0x0f];
        s0 = sigma3(s0);
        s1 = work_space[(i + 14) & 0x0f];
        s1 = sigma4(s1);
        t1 = work_space[i & 0xf] += s0 + s1 + work_space[(i + 9) & 0xf];
        t1 += h + sigma2(e) + ch(e, f, g) + k256[i];
        t2 = sigma1(a) + maj(a, b, c);
        h = g;
        g = f;
        f = e;
        e = d + t1;
        d = c;
        c = b;
        b = a;
        a = t1 + t2;
    }

    iv[0] += a;
    iv[1] += b;
    iv[2] += c;
    iv[3] += d;
    iv[4] += e;
    iv[5] += f;
    iv[6] += g;
    iv[7] += h;
}

int sha256_init(Sha256 *self)
{
    /* input sanity check: */
    if (!self)
    {
        return -1;
    }

    memset(self, 0, sizeof(*self));
    self->iv[0] = 0x6a09e667;
    self->iv[1] = 0xbb67ae85;
    self->iv[2] = 0x3c6ef372;
    self->iv[3] = 0xa54ff53a;
    self->iv[4] = 0x510e527f;
    self->iv[5] = 0x9b05688c;
    self->iv[6] = 0x1f83d9ab;
    self->iv[7] = 0x5be0cd19;

    return 0;
}

int sha256_update(Sha256 *self, const uint8_t *data, size_t datalen)
{
    uint32_t lo;

    if ((!self) || (!data) || (!datalen))
    {
        return -1;
    }

    while (datalen-- > 0)
    {
        self->leftover[self->leftover_offset++] = *(data++);
        if (self->leftover_offset >= SHA256_BLOCK_SIZE)
        {
            compress(self->iv, self->leftover);
            self->leftover_offset = 0;
            lo = self->bits_hashed[0] + (SHA256_BLOCK_SIZE << 3);
            if (lo < self->bits_hashed[0])
                self->bits_hashed[1] += 1;
            self->bits_hashed[0] = lo;
        }
    }
    return 0;
}

int sha256_final(Sha256 *self, uint8_t digest[32])
{
    uint32_t i, lo;

    if (!digest || !self)
    {
        return -1;
    }

    lo = self->bits_hashed[0] + (self->leftover_offset << 3);
    if (lo < self->bits_hashed[0])
        self->bits_hashed[1] += 1;
    self->bits_hashed[0] = lo;

    self->leftover[self->leftover_offset++] = 0x80;
    if (self->leftover_offset > (sizeof(self->leftover) - 8))
    {
        memset(self->leftover + self->leftover_offset, 0x00, sizeof(self->leftover) - self->leftover_offset);
        compress(self->iv, self->leftover);
        self->leftover_offset = 0;
    }

    memset(self->leftover + self->leftover_offset, 0x00, sizeof(self->leftover) - 8 - self->leftover_offset);
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 1] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[0]);
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 2] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[0] >> 8);
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 3] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[0] >> 16);
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 4] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[0] >> 24);
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 5] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[1] );
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 6] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[1] >> 8);
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 7] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[1] >> 16);
    self->leftover[sizeof(self->leftover) - 8] = (uint8_t)(self->bits_hashed[1] >> 24);

    compress(self->iv, self->leftover);

    for (i = 0; i < SHA256_STATE_BLOCKS; ++i)
    {
        // uint32_t t = *((uint32_t *)&self->iv[i]);
        uint32_t t = self->iv[i];
        *digest++ = (uint8_t
)(t >> 24);
        *digest++ = (uint8_t)(t >> 16);
        *digest++ = (uint8_t)(t >> 8);
        *digest++ = (uint8_t)(t);
    }
    memset(self, 0, sizeof(*self));
    return 0;
}

typedef struct Sha256
```
